</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWhen you think about the full spi=
rit of what this crypto revolution is, there=E2=80=99s something pure in wh=
at Dogecoin has done,=E2=80=9D Mike Novogratz, founder of Galaxy Digital Ho=
ldings, said on CNBC. =E2=80=9CI worry that once the enthusiasm rolls out, =
there are no developers, there=E2=80=99s no institutions coming in. But it=
=E2=80=99s got the moniker of the people=E2=80=99s coin right now and it=E2=
=80=99d be very dangerous to be short.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px=
 0;">The overnight gain took Dogecoin=E2=80=99s one-week advance to 118% an=
d its value to $87 billion in Wednesday trading, according to CoinMarketCap=
.com data, eclipsing the largest exchange-traded gold fund and even stocks =
like Fedex Corp. and Snap Inc. A year ago, the asset was worth just $315 mi=
llion. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CAt some point, so=
mething is just real,=E2=80=9D said Sam Bankman-Fried, the Hong Kong-based =
chief executive officer of the FTX crypto exchange. =E2=80=9CIf Dogecoin is=
 stupid and valueless, it shouldn=E2=80=99t be worth $90 billion. How about=
 gold or Bitcoin or euros? Our collective imagination has given them value,=
 and now we just think about them having value.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"mar=
gin: 16px 0;">Dogecoin, started in 2013 as a joke based on the Shiba Inu br=
eed of dog, may become so accepted by the mainstream it might evolve into a=
 payment option at retailers, Bankman-Fried said. At Blockfolio, a firm own=
ed by FTX that helps users manage their crypto portfolios, trading volumes =
are spiking with Dogecoin=E2=80=99s every gain, a sign it=E2=80=99s become =
essential to the whole ecosystem. ...</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">While=
 it=E2=80=99s difficult to assign firm reasons to Dogecoin=E2=80=99s ascent=
, a few factors have fueled the gains. On April 20, a day normally associat=
ed with pot, some users got #DogeDay trending to push up the price. Celebri=
ties from Musk to the Dallas Mavericks=E2=80=99 billionaire owner Mark Cuba=
n also jumped on the bandwagon. The Gemini crypto exchange backed by the Wi=
nklevoss twins announced Tuesday it will soon enable trading of the coin.</=
p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Just imagine traveling 10 years=
 back in time and trying to explain=C2=A0this to someone; just imagine what=
 an idiot you=E2=80=99d feel like. =E2=80=9CThere=E2=80=99s going to be thi=
s online currency that people think is a form of digital gold, and then the=
re=E2=80=99s going to be a <em>different</em>=C2=A0online currency that is =
a parody of the first one based on a meme about a talking Shiba Inu, and th=
at one will have a market capitalization bigger than 80% of the companies i=
n the S&amp;P 500, and its value will=C2=A0fluctuate based on things like w=
ho is hosting =E2=80=98Saturday Night Live=E2=80=99 and whether people twee=
t a hashtag about it on the pot-joke holiday, and Bloomberg will write arti=
cles and banks will write research notes about those sorts of catalysts, an=
d it will remain a perfectly=C2=A0ridiculous content-free parody even as pe=
ople properly take it completely seriously because there are billions of do=
llars at stake.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For that matter, i=
magine being me, now, and trying to say something interesting about this; j=
ust imagine what an idiot I feel like.=C2=A0I hope Elon Musk is funny on SN=
L! That will make the value of Dogecoin go up! Me, I want to write about <a=
 href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/23761771.258996/aHR0=
