LXJlLWJvcmVkLXlvdS1jYW4tdHJhZGUtc3RvY2tz/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB0ac93107"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  boredom=
 markets hypothesis</a> says that people will buy stocks when buying stocks=
 is more fun than other things they could be doing for fun.</li>=09<li styl=
e=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusines=
s.com/click/23761771.258996/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2F=
ydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDItMDgvZWxvbi1tdXNrLXdvcmtzLWhpcy1tYWdpYy1vbi1kb2dlY29pbi=
1hbmQtYml0Y29pbg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd53b5078" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" =
itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  Elon markets hypothesis</a> say=
s =E2=80=9Cthat things are valuable not based on their cash flows but on th=
eir proximity to Elon Musk.=E2=80=9D</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=
Are those hypotheses self-limiting in some way? The point of the BMH (bored=
om markets hypothesis) was that as pandemic lockdowns eased, people would g=
o back to doing things that are actually fun, and spend less time day-tradi=
ng stocks. But I did not fully reckon with the possibility that people woul=
d spend the pandemic lockdowns not just trading stocks, but also=C2=A0<em>m=
aking it more fun</em> to trade stocks. Partly that is by making the tradin=
g experience more fun and social, with Reddit boards and sea chanteys to ma=
ke your favorite stock a bit more exciting. Partly it is by finding more fu=
n things to trade than stocks; why buy Tesla Inc. stock when you can buy an=
 imaginary coin named after a Shiba Inu meme that Elon Musk will tout on =
=E2=80=98Saturday Night Live=E2=80=99? Partly it is just through the tradit=
ional way that trading is sometimes fun:=C2=A0<em>Everything keeps going up=
</em>, so it is fun to buy the things because you make money.</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I suppose the boredom-driven rally ends through some c=
ombination of (1) people can do normal fun things again and (2) like, Dogec=
oin drops for fundamental reasons (?) and it stops being free money all the=
 time?</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The point of the E'MH (E-prime MH, E=
lon markets hypothesis, to distinguish it from the efficient markets hypoth=
esis, which owns the rights to =E2=80=9CEMH=E2=80=9D) is not too dissimilar=
: Elon Musk combines the concepts of =E2=80=9Cget rich=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=
=9Chave fun=E2=80=9D in an unusual way. I once <a href=3D"https://link.mail=
.bloombergbusiness.com/click/23761771.258996/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLm=
NvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDItMDgvZWxvbi1tdXNrLXdvcmtzLWhpcy1tYWdpY=
y1vbi1kb2dlY29pbi1hbmQtYml0Y29pbg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cCd53b5078" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> wrote</a>:</p><=
blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Musk is the richest person in the w=
orld, and in a dynamic, fun, traveling-to-Mars sort of way. It makes sense =
that his pronouncements have a certain religious character, that his tweets=
 can endow arbitrary objects with <em>mana</em>. If the richest person in t=
he world tweets =E2=80=9CGamestonk!=E2=80=9D then I think that means that, =
if you buy GameStop stock, you will partake in his wealth and dynamism at a=
 remove; you will get rich and have fun doing it. (Not! Investing! Advice!)=
=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Again, when his advice =
stops working to make people rich, or when there are more fun things to do,=
